  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>This technique must be used after successfully knocking a target into the air with Kage Buyou. Make an unarmed attack against the target, which gains a critical threat range increase of +1 and deals triple damage on hit. If hit, the target is @Condition[stunned]{stunned} for 1d6 rounds (Fortitude negates), is thrown down to the ground and knocked @Condition[prone]{prone}, and may not make a Tumble check to reduce or avoid fall damage.<br><br>You will land in a square adjacent to the target, and will become @Condition[exhausted]{exhausted} for the remainder of the encounter, plus 5 minutes afterwards. A Fortitude save (DC 21) allows you to be @Condition[fatigued]{fatigued} instead.</p>\n\n\n\n",
